%N A397478 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=0} binomial(2*k, k)/(2^(3*k)*(2*k+1)^4).
%H A397478 Nandan Sai Dasireddy, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/10652469.2024.2339854">Solution to a problem involving central binomial coefficients</a>, Integral Transforms and Special Functions, Vol. 35, No. 9 (2024), pp. 457-462.
%H A397478 Steven R. Finch, <a href="https://compmath.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/central_binomial_coefficients_finch.pdf">Central Binomial Coefficients</a>, 2007. See p. 5.
%F A397478 Equals 5F4([1/2, 1/2, 1/2, 1/2, 1/2], [3/2, 3/2, 3/2, 3/2], 1/2), where 5F4 is a generalized hypergeometric function.
%F A397478 Equals sqrt(2)*Pi^3*log(2)/768 + sqrt(2)*Pi*zeta(3)/16 - sqrt(2)*(psi'''(1/4) - 8*Pi^4)/6144 - sqrt(2)/2*Im(polylog(4, 1 - i)), where psi'''(1/4) is the third derivative of the digamma function at 1/4 (A390074), and i is the imaginary unit (Dasireddy, 2024).
%e A397478 1.003255988082482401733062347197855657327349016084392...
%t A397478 RealDigits[Sqrt[2]*Pi^3*Log[2]/768 + Sqrt[2]*Pi*Zeta[3]/16 - Sqrt[2]*(PolyGamma[3, 1/4] - 8*Pi^4)/6144 - Sqrt[2]/2*Im[PolyLog[4, 1 - I]], 10, 120][[1]]
%o A397478 (PARI) sqrt(2)*Pi^3*log(2)/768 + sqrt(2)*Pi*zeta(3)/16 - sqrt(2)*(psi'''(1/4) - 8*Pi^4)/6144 - sqrt(2)/2*imag(polylog(4, 1 - I))
%Y A397478 Sum_{k>=0} binomial(2*k, k)/(2^(3*k)*(2*k+1)^m): A002193 (m=0), A093954 (m=1), A263353 (m=2), A397477 (m=3), this constant (m=4).
%Y A397478 Cf. A000984, A002117, A002162, A390074.
